BETSY was once a very common nickname for Elizabeth, but you hardly hear it anymore.  Of course, we have the legendary Betsy Ross in our early history, who supposedly sewed the first US flag (spoiler alert:  she didn't), and the nickname continued to be used into the mid-20th century.  If you come across a BETSY these days, she's probably in her 90s.

